cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.PL 

The paper deals with complexity results for computational problems related to graphs and logic, which are typical topics in computer science theory (cs.CC). The use of a nondeterministic model of computation and the focus on motion-planning problems suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the study of planar graphs and highly restricted vertex configurations, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of constraints and logic in the model of computation suggests a connection to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of decision problems, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
